Creating a simple web application that generates a fantasy language vocabulary and grammar based on user input using Chomsky notation involves some creativity. Below is an HTML file that includes CSS for styling and JavaScript for functionality. The web app takes user input and generates a set of vocabulary and grammatical rules.

You can copy and paste the following code into an HTML file and open it in your web browser.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Fantasy Language Creator</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 20px;
            background-color: #f0f0f0;
        }
        h1 {
            color: #4a4a4a;
        }
        input[type="text"], textarea {
            width: 100%;
            padding: 10px;
            margin: 10px 0;
        }
        button {
            padding: 10px 20px;
            background-color: #5cb85c;
            color: white;
            border: none;
            cursor: pointer;
        }
        button:hover {
            background-color: #4cae4c;
        }
        #output {
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            padding: 10px;
            background-color: white;
            margin-top: 20px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<h1>Fantasy Language Creator</h1>
<p>Enter a base word or phrase to generate a fantasy vocabulary and grammar structure.</p>
<input type="text" id="inputString" placeholder="Enter a word or phrase">
<button onclick="generateLanguage()">Generate Language</button>

<div id="output"></div>

<script>
    function generateLanguage() {
        const input = document.getElementById('inputString').value.trim();
        if (!input) {
            alert('Please enter a word or phrase!');
            return;
        }

        // Simple transformation rules
        const base = input.split(' ');
        const vocabulary = base.map(word => transformWord(word)).join(', ');
        const grammarRules = generateGrammar(base.length);

        // Display results
        document.getElementById('output').innerHTML = `
            <h2>Vocabulary:</h2>
            <p>${vocabulary}</p>
            <h2>Grammar Rules:</h2>
            <p>${grammarRules}</p>
        `;
    }

    function transformWord(word) {
        const suffixes = ['na', 'or', 'il', 'en', 'am', 'os'];

        // Create a fantasy word by appending a random suffix
        return word + suffixes[Math.floor(Math.random() * suffixes.length)];
    }

    function generateGrammar(numWords) {
        const rules = [];
        for (let i = 1; i <= numWords; i++) {
            rules.push(`S -> NP VP | S Conj S`);
            rules.push(`NP -> Det N | N`);
            rules.push(`VP -> V NP | V NP PP`);
            rules.push(`PP -> P NP`);
        }
        return rules.join('<br>');
    }
</script>

</body>
</html>
```

### Explanation:

1. ** HTML Structure**:
   - The file consists of a simple layout where the user can input a word or phrase.
   - It has a button to trigger the generation of the vocabulary and grammar.

2. **CSS Styles**:
   - Basic styles are added to make the application visually appealing.

3. **JavaScript Functionality**:
   - When the user clicks the "Generate Language" button, the `generateLanguage` function is called.
   - This takes the user input, splits it into words, and generates a fantasy vocabulary by transforming each word.
   - It also generates simple grammatical rules based on the number of words in the input.
   - The resulting vocabulary and grammar rules are displayed in the output area.

You can modify the rules and vocabulary transformation functions to create a more unique fantasy language as per your requirements!

